$\\sim$640$\\K$. Moreover, it appears that larger dust grains are preferred in\nquasars. The lower dust temperature and smaller grain sizes inferred for these\nthree galaxies compared with that of quasars could be due to the fact that they\nmay harbor a young/weak AGN which is not maturely developed yet.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 12 Jul 2015 22:26:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-06"}
